extras.diff:
--- /workspace/paper_writer.py
+++ /workspace/paper_writer.py
@@ -0,0 +1,2 @@
+import json
+import random
@@ -1,0 +4,49 @@
+def generate_paper(topic):
+    # Generate random data for the paper
+    authors = ["Alice Smith", "Bob Johnson", "Charlie Brown"]
+    universities = ["Stanford University", "MIT", "Harvard University"]
+    methods = ["double-blind study", "longitudinal analysis", "cross-sectional survey"]
+    results = ["significant improvement", "no noticeable effect", "mild degradation"]
+
+    # Paper structure
+    paper = {
+        "title": topic["title"],
+        "authors": random.sample(authors, 2),
+        "affiliation": random.choice(universities),
+        "abstract": f"This study examines {topic['title'].lower()}. Our {random.choice(methods)} shows {random.choice(results)}.",
+        "sections": {}
+    }
+
+    # Generate content for each section
+    for section in topic["sections"]:
+        if section == "Introduction":
+            paper["sections"][section] = f"{topic['title']} has become increasingly relevant in modern society. We review existing literature and propose a novel approach."
+        elif section == "Methodology":
+            paper["sections"][section] = f"We conducted a {random.choice(methods)} with {random.randint(50, 200)} participants over {random.randint(1, 12)} months."
+        elif section == "Results":
+            paper["sections"][section] = f"Our analysis revealed {random.choice(results)} (p < 0.0{random.randint(1, 5)})."
+        elif section == "Conclusion":
+            paper["sections"][section] = "These findings suggest important implications for future research and practical applications."
+        elif section == "References":
+            paper["sections"][section] = "1. Smith et al. (2020)\n2. Johnson (2018)\n3. Brown & Lee (2019)"
+
+    return paper
+
+def generate_latex(paper):
+    latex = f"\\documentclass{{article}}\n\\title{{{paper['title']}}}\n\\author{{{' and '.join(paper['authors'])}}}\n\\date{{\\today}}\n\n\\begin{{document}}\n\n\\maketitle\n\n\\section*{{Abstract}}\n{paper['abstract']}\n\n"
+
+    for section, content in paper['sections'].items():
+        if section != "Abstract":
+            latex += f"\\section{{{section}}}\n{content}\n\n"
+
+    latex += "\\end{document}"
+    return latex
+
+if __name__ == "__main__":
+    # Load sample topic
+    with open("/workspace/topic.json") as f:
+        topic = json.load(f)
+
+    # Generate and print LaTeX paper
+    paper = generate_paper(topic)
+    print(generate_latex(paper))
